Sentencas: The phase relation, diffusivity, and electrical conductivity are investigated for powders and dense crystalline bodies of manganese-chromium-iron oxides with spinel structure which is regarded as main compounds in the oxide scale of some ferritic alloy interconnects of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Structure and transport property of manganese-chromium-iron oxide as a main compound in oxide scales of alloy interconnects for SOFCs

Sentencas: The lattice parameter of MnCr2O4-based spinel oxide increased with iron substitution for chromium at B-site.
Titulo: Structure and transport property of manganese-chromium-iron oxide as a main compound in oxide scales of alloy interconnects for SOFCs

Sentencas: The iron substitution greatly improved the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Structure and transport property of manganese-chromium-iron oxide as a main compound in oxide scales of alloy interconnects for SOFCs

Sentencas: The fast cation diffusion was observed for iron substituted samples forming an iron-rich layer in the vicinity of surface.
Titulo: Structure and transport property of manganese-chromium-iron oxide as a main compound in oxide scales of alloy interconnects for SOFCs

Sentencas: The compatibility of some ferritic alloys as SOFC interconnects is evaluated by using conductivity data of Mn-Cr-Fe spinels.
Titulo: Structure and transport property of manganese-chromium-iron oxide as a main compound in oxide scales of alloy interconnects for SOFCs
